{"title_page": "YBN (collective)", "text_new": "{{short description|American hip-hop group}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = YBN\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = YBN Nahmir (26100131778) (cropped).png\n| caption          = [[YBN Nahmir]] (left) and YBN Glizzy performing together in January 2018\n| origin           = [[Birmingham, Alabama|Birmingham]], [[Alabama]], U.S.\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n* [[Trap Music|trap]]\n}}\n| label            =\n{{flatlist|\n* [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n* Art@War {{small|(current)}}\n* YBN\n}}\n| current_members  = See [[#Members|Members]]\n| years_active = 2014&ndash;present\n}}\n'''YBN''', short for '''Young Boss Niggas''' is an American [[Musical collective|hip-hop collective]] formed by Nick Simmons, who goes by the stage name [[YBN Nahmir]]. \"<ref name=\":1\">{{Citation|last=REAL 92.3 LA|title=YBN Nahmir Talks Going To Prom, Sleeping w/ 30 Year Olds, \"Rubbin Off The Paint\"|date=2017-12-04|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cFybIXGLfb4|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref> YBN is a collective of rappers, record producers, social media personalities and promoters.<ref name=\"fader\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/05/24/all-the-members-of-ybn-nahmir-ybn-cordae-ybn-almighty-jay/ybn-malik|title=Meet all the members of YBN, a new kind of internet rap clique|work=The FADER|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref> The collective has members from Africa, Alabama, Texas, California, Maryland, Narberth, and Connecticut.\n\nOn September 7, 2018, YBN released their first full-length project together, ''YBN: The Mixtape'', which featured collaborations with [[Gucci Mane]], [[Wiz Khalifa]], [[Lil Skies]], [[Machine Gun Kelly (rapper)|Machine Gun Kelly]] and [[Chris Brown]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/09/07/ybn-the-mixtape-stream|title=Listen to YBN\u2019s debut mixtape|work=The FADER|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/09/ybn-almighty-jay-cordae-nahmir-mixtape-stream|title=YBN Crew Releases New Mixtape f/ Gucci Mane, R Kelly, Lil Skies, and More|website=Complex|language=en|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref><ref name=\"YBNMixtape\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/ybn-the-mixtape/1435508126|title=YBN: The Mixtape by YBN Almighty Jay, YBN Cordae & YBN Nahmir|work=Apple Music|date=September 7, 2018|accessdate=July 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nIn 2014, Nick Simmons, better known as [[YBN Nahmir]], met YBN Almighty Jay on the video game [[Grand Theft Auto V]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/ybn-nahmir-jay-almighty-ybn-cordae-breakdown/|title=A Guide to the YBN Crew: Rap's Most Exciting New Prospects|date=2018-09-09|work=Highsnobiety|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en-US}}</ref> Nahmir later introduced Almighty Jay to his close friend YBN Glizzy, that he met on a San Andreas roleplay for [[Grand Theft Auto Online]] through an [[Xbox]] Looking for Group post.<ref>{{Citation|last=YBN Glizzy|title=Ayo Glizzy - WORST SA-MP Player FT. Nahmir|date=2015-02-15|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1GSJv4cqKTE|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref>\n\nYBN was originally a gaming collective where Nahmir and his friends played video games, recorded videos and uploaded their videos to [[YouTube]] and streamed on [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2017/10/18/ybn-nahmir-interview-rubbin-off-the-paint|title=How YBN Nahmir went from gamer kid to rising rapper|work=The FADER|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref> In 2015, Nahmir and Almighty Jay eventually decided to record a song after [[Freestyle rap|freestyling]] in Xbox Live group chats. The song, titled \"Hood Mentality\", was both of the artists' first song, and the start of the collective's move away from video games and towards music.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2017/11/ybn-nahmir-interview-the-break/|title=The Break Presents: YBN Nahmir - XXL|website=XXL Mag|language=en|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref> In 2015, crew member YBN Valley died due to a heart attack.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/video/2017/11/ybn-nahmir-letter-to-valley-part-5-video/|title=YBN Nahmir Releases ''Letter to Valley Part 5'' Video - XXL|website=XXL Mag|language=en|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref>\n\nOn September 18, 2017, Nahmir's debut single, \"[[Rubbin Off the Paint]]\", was released, and the music video premiered on WorldStarHipHop. The single featured production by Izak<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8475033/ybn-the-mixtape-review-ybn-nahmir-ybn-almighty-jay-ybn-cordae|title=YBN Nahmir, YBN Almighty Jay & YBN Cordae Showcase Potential as a Formidable Trio on 'YBN: The Mixtape'|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> and went viral, peaking at number 46 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 chart. Nahmir used the financial success of the song to move himself to Los Angeles, California and help fellow friends in the collective also move to Los Angeles, marking the first time they had met in person.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nFellow members of the collective soon started to have viral songs too, though none charted. YBN Almighty Jay's \"Chopsticks\" in November 2017,<ref>{{Citation|last=Waterwippinevan|title=YBN Almighty Jay \"Chopsticks\" (Official Video) dir. by @waterwippinevan|date=2017-11-10|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q-hN8TvIee8|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref> YBN Walker's \"Gutta\" in February 2018, and YBN NickyBaandz \"Been Trippin\" in April 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/05/24/all-the-members-of-ybn-nahmir-ybn-cordae-ybn-almighty-jay/ybn-carl|title=Meet all the members of YBN, a new kind of internet rap clique|work=The FADER|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref>\n\nYBN Nahmir and YBN Glizzy met Cordae Amari Dunston, better known as [[YBN Cordae]], online in 2017. Though Cordae didn't play video games, he had been rapping longer than any other member of YBN and was older than the rest of the collective. He decided to formally join the collective in 2018 and, in May 2018, released a remix of Eminem's \"My Name Is\"<ref>{{Citation|last=WORLDSTARHIPHOP|title=YBN Cordae \"My Name Is\" (Eminem Remix) (WSHH Exclusive - Official Music Video)|date=2018-05-09|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=07tFOl-9Av4|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://hypebeast.com/2018/5/ybn-cordae-eminem-my-name-is-remix|title=YBN Cordae Remixes Eminem's \"My Name Is\"|work=HYPEBEAST|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref> which quickly went viral. He followed up with his breakout single, \"Old Niggas\", a remix and direct response to the song \"1985 - (Intro to \"The Fall Off)\" by [[J. Cole]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/05/ybn-cordae-is-latest-rapper-to-respond-to-j-cole-1985|title=YBN Cordae Is the Latest Rapper to Respond to J. Cole's \"1985\"|website=Complex|language=en|access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> The song was mentioned on multiple publications such as ''[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/07/ybn-cordae-interview-the-break/|title=The Break Presents: YBN Cordae - XXL|work=XXL Mag|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref>[[XXL (magazine)|,]] ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://pigeonsandplanes.com/interviews/2018/05/ybn-cordae-interview|title=Bridging Rap's Generational Divide: An Interview With YBN Cordae|work=PigeonsandPlanes|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref> and ''[[HipHopDX]].''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.46877/title.ybn-cordae-challenges-j-coles-1985-criticisms-on-old-niggas|title=YBN Cordae Challenges J. Cole's \"1985\" Criticisms On \"Old Niggas\"|last=http://hiphopdx.com|first=HipHopDX -|work=HipHopDX|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nThe group announced their first world tour in July 2018, scheduled for Fall 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/07/ybn-nahmir-ybn-almighty-jay-ybn-cordae-european-tour/|title=YBN Nahmir Shares Dates for European Tour  - XXL|website=XXL Mag|language=en|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref> The group's first full-length project, titled ''YBN: The Mixtape,'' which starred Nahmir, Almighty Jay and Cordae, was announced in August 2018 and was released on September 7, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/08/ybn-nahmir-ybn-mixtape-release-date/|title=YBN Nahmir Sets Release Date for YBN Mixtape - XXL|work=XXL Mag|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2018/09/ybn-ybn-the-mixtape-ybn-nahmir-ybn-cordae-ybn-almighty-jay-wiz-khalifa/|title=YBN Nahmir, YBN Cordae and YBN Almighty Jay 'YBN: The Mixtape' - XXL|work=XXL Mag|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref> It included the singles \"Rubbin Off The Paint\" (Nahmir), \"Bounce Out With That\" (Nahmir), \"Chopsticks\" (Almighty Jay), \"Bread Winners\" (Nahmir and Almighty Jay), and \"Kung Fu\" (Cordae).\n\n== Members ==\nYBN consists of multiple members, with three core members, namely:\n* [[YBN Nahmir]]\n* YBN Almighty Jay\n* [[YBN Cordae]]\n\nOther members include: \n{{Div col|colwidth=16em}}\n* YBN Prinse Moe\n* YBN AP\n* YBN MOMO\n* YBN Glizzy\n* YBN Manny\n* YBN Xanny\n* YBN Mcfadden\n* YBN Jmore\n* YBN Choppa\n* YBN Ballout\n* YBN Al\n* YBN Carl\n* YBN Nicky\n* YBN FRESH\n* YBN ZHY\n* YBN Lonzo\n* YBN Dayday\n* YBN OJONG\n* YBN Lil E\n* YBN Luigi\n* YBN DVD\n* YBN r0yal\n* YBN Declan\n* YBN Swarn\n* YBN Mirr\n* YBN Naim\n* YBN Antsu\n* YBN Future Savage\n* YBN WOODRYC\n* YBN 5cxxt\n* YBN Ray\n{{Div col end}}\nDeceased members:\n* YBN Valley\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Mixtapes ==ybn dixon=\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+ List of mixtapes, with selected chart positions and details\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:19em;\" | Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Certifications\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard 200|US]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-200/2018-09-22|title=Billboard 200 \u2013 September 22, 2018|work=Billboard|accessdate=July 26, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|US R&B/HH]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/r-b-hip-hop-albums/2018-09-22|title=Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums \u2013 September 22, 2018|work=Billboard|accessdate=July 26, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Top Rap Albums|US<br>Rap]]<br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/rap-albums/2018-09-22|title=Top Rap Albums \u2013 September 22, 2018|work=Billboard|accessdate=July 26, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/canadian-albums/2018-09-22|title=Canadian Albums Chart \u2013 September 22, 2018|work=Billboard|accessdate=July 26, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''YBN: The Mixtape''<br/><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(with YBN Almighty Jay, [[YBN Cordae]] and [[YBN Nahmir]])</span> YBN woodryc & \n\nybn 5cxtt \n|\n* Released: September 7, 2018<ref name=\"YBNMixtape\"/>\n* Label: YBN\n* Formats: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n\n<br />\n| 21 || 13 || 12 || 19\n|\n* RIAA: Gold<ref name=\"RIAA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&se=YBN+Nahmir#search_section|title=American certifications \u2013 YBN Nahmir|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]|accessdate=July 31, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Hip hop collectives]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2014]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American hip-hop group}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = YBN\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = YBN Nahmir (26100131778) (cropped).png\n| caption          = [[YBN Nahmir]] (left) and YBN Glizzy performing together in January 2018\n| origin           = [[Birmingham, Alabama|Birmingham]], [[Alabama]], U.S.\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n* [[Trap Music|trap]]\n}}\n| label            =\n{{flatlist|\n* [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n* Art@War {{small|(current)}}\n* YBN\n}}\n| current_members  = See [[#Members|Members]]\n| years_active = 2014&ndash;present\n}}\n'''YBN''', short for '''Young Boss Niggas''' is an American [[Musical collective|hip-hop collective]] formed by Nick Simmons, who goes by the stage name [[YBN Nahmir]]. \"<ref name=\":1\">{{Citation|last=REAL 92.3 LA|title=YBN Nahmir Talks Going To Prom, Sleeping w/ 30 Year Olds, \"Rubbin Off The Paint\"|date=2017-12-04|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cFybIXGLfb4|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref> YBN is a collective of rappers, record producers, social media personalities and promoters.<ref name=\"fader\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/05/24/all-the-members-of-ybn-nahmir-ybn-cordae-ybn-almighty-jay/ybn-malik|title=Meet all the members of YBN, a new kind of internet rap clique|work=The FADER|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref> The collective has members from Africa, Alabama, Texas, California, Maryland, Narberth, and Connecticut.\n\nOn September 7, 2018, YBN released their first full-length project together, ''YBN: The Mixtape'', which featured collaborations with [[Gucci Mane]], [[Wiz Khalifa]], [[Lil Skies]], [[Machine Gun Kelly (rapper)|Machine Gun Kelly]] and [[Chris Brown]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/09/07/ybn-the-mixtape-stream|title=Listen to YBN\u2019s debut mixtape|work=The FADER|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/09/ybn-almighty-jay-cordae-nahmir-mixtape-stream|title=YBN Crew Releases New Mixtape f/ Gucci Mane, R Kelly, Lil Skies, and More|website=Complex|language=en|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref><ref name=\"YBNMixtape\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/ybn-the-mixtape/1435508126|title=YBN: The Mixtape by YBN Almighty Jay, YBN Cordae & YBN Nahmir|work=Apple Music|date=September 7, 2018|accessdate=July 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nIn 2014, Nick Simmons, better known as [[YBN Nahmir]], met YBN Almighty Jay on the video game [[Grand Theft Auto V]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/ybn-nahmir-jay-almighty-ybn-cordae-breakdown/|title=A Guide to the YBN Crew: Rap's Most Exciting New Prospects|date=2018-09-09|work=Highsnobiety|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en-US}}</ref> Nahmir later introduced Almighty Jay to his close friend YBN Glizzy, that he met on a San Andreas roleplay for [[Grand Theft Auto Online]] through an [[Xbox]] Looking for Group post.<ref>{{Citation|last=YBN Glizzy|title=Ayo Glizzy - WORST SA-MP Player FT. Nahmir|date=2015-02-15|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1GSJv4cqKTE|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref>\n\nYBN was originally a gaming collective where Nahmir and his friends played video games, recorded videos and uploaded their videos to [[YouTube]] and streamed on [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2017/10/18/ybn-nahmir-interview-rubbin-off-the-paint|title=How YBN Nahmir went from gamer kid to rising rapper|work=The FADER|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref> In 2015, Nahmir and Almighty Jay eventually decided to record a song after [[Freestyle rap|freestyling]] in Xbox Live group chats. The song, titled \"Hood Mentality\", was both of the artists' first song, and the start of the collective's move away from video games and towards music.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2017/11/ybn-nahmir-interview-the-break/|title=The Break Presents: YBN Nahmir - XXL|website=XXL Mag|language=en|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref> In 2015, crew member YBN Valley died due to a heart attack.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/video/2017/11/ybn-nahmir-letter-to-valley-part-5-video/|title=YBN Nahmir Releases ''Letter to Valley Part 5'' Video - XXL|website=XXL Mag|language=en|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref>\n\nOn September 18, 2017, Nahmir's debut single, \"[[Rubbin Off the Paint]]\", was released, and the music video premiered on WorldStarHipHop. The single featured production by Izak<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8475033/ybn-the-mixtape-review-ybn-nahmir-ybn-almighty-jay-ybn-cordae|title=YBN Nahmir, YBN Almighty Jay & YBN Cordae Showcase Potential as a Formidable Trio on 'YBN: The Mixtape'|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> and went viral, peaking at number 46 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 chart. Nahmir used the financial success of the song to move himself to Los Angeles, California and help fellow friends in the collective also move to Los Angeles, marking the first time they had met in person.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nFellow members of the collective soon started to have viral songs too, though none charted. YBN Almighty Jay's \"Chopsticks\" in November 2017,<ref>{{Citation|last=Waterwippinevan|title=YBN Almighty Jay \"Chopsticks\" (Official Video) dir. by @waterwippinevan|date=2017-11-10|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q-hN8TvIee8|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref> YBN Walker's \"Gutta\" in February 2018, and YBN NickyBaandz \"Been Trippin\" in April 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/05/24/all-the-members-of-ybn-nahmir-ybn-cordae-ybn-almighty-jay/ybn-carl|title=Meet all the members of YBN, a new kind of internet rap clique|work=The FADER|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref>\n\nYBN Nahmir and YBN Glizzy met Cordae Amari Dunston, better known as [[YBN Cordae]], online in 2017. Though Cordae didn't play video games, he had been rapping longer than any other member of YBN and was older than the rest of the collective. He decided to formally join the collective in 2018 and, in May 2018, released a remix of Eminem's \"My Name Is\"<ref>{{Citation|last=WORLDSTARHIPHOP|title=YBN Cordae \"My Name Is\" (Eminem Remix) (WSHH Exclusive - Official Music Video)|date=2018-05-09|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=07tFOl-9Av4|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://hypebeast.com/2018/5/ybn-cordae-eminem-my-name-is-remix|title=YBN Cordae Remixes Eminem's \"My Name Is\"|work=HYPEBEAST|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref> which quickly went viral. He followed up with his breakout single, \"Old Niggas\", a remix and direct response to the song \"1985 - (Intro to \"The Fall Off)\" by [[J. Cole]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/05/ybn-cordae-is-latest-rapper-to-respond-to-j-cole-1985|title=YBN Cordae Is the Latest Rapper to Respond to J. Cole's \"1985\"|website=Complex|language=en|access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> The song was mentioned on multiple publications such as ''[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/07/ybn-cordae-interview-the-break/|title=The Break Presents: YBN Cordae - XXL|work=XXL Mag|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref>[[XXL (magazine)|,]] ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://pigeonsandplanes.com/interviews/2018/05/ybn-cordae-interview|title=Bridging Rap's Generational Divide: An Interview With YBN Cordae|work=PigeonsandPlanes|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref> and ''[[HipHopDX]].''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.46877/title.ybn-cordae-challenges-j-coles-1985-criticisms-on-old-niggas|title=YBN Cordae Challenges J. Cole's \"1985\" Criticisms On \"Old Niggas\"|last=http://hiphopdx.com|first=HipHopDX -|work=HipHopDX|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nThe group announced their first world tour in July 2018, scheduled for Fall 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/07/ybn-nahmir-ybn-almighty-jay-ybn-cordae-european-tour/|title=YBN Nahmir Shares Dates for European Tour  - XXL|website=XXL Mag|language=en|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref> The group's first full-length project, titled ''YBN: The Mixtape,'' which starred Nahmir, Almighty Jay and Cordae, was announced in August 2018 and was released on September 7, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/08/ybn-nahmir-ybn-mixtape-release-date/|title=YBN Nahmir Sets Release Date for YBN Mixtape - XXL|work=XXL Mag|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2018/09/ybn-ybn-the-mixtape-ybn-nahmir-ybn-cordae-ybn-almighty-jay-wiz-khalifa/|title=YBN Nahmir, YBN Cordae and YBN Almighty Jay 'YBN: The Mixtape' - XXL|work=XXL Mag|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en}}</ref> It included the singles \"Rubbin Off The Paint\" (Nahmir), \"Bounce Out With That\" (Nahmir), \"Chopsticks\" (Almighty Jay), \"Bread Winners\" (Nahmir and Almighty Jay), and \"Kung Fu\" (Cordae).\n\n== Members ==\nYBN consists of multiple members, with three core members, namely:\n* [[YBN Nahmir]]\n* YBN Almighty Jay\n* [[YBN Cordae]]\n\nOther members include: \n{{Div col|colwidth=16em}}\n* YBN Prinse Moe\n* YBN AP\n* YBN MOMO\n* YBN Glizzy\n* YBN Manny\n* YBN Xanny\n* YBN Mcfadden\n* YBN Jmore\n* YBN Choppa\n* YBN Ballout\n* YBN Al\n* YBN Carl\n* YBN Nicky\n* YBN FRESH\n* YBN ZHY\n* YBN Lonzo\n* YBN Dayday\n* YBN OJONG\n* YBN Lil E\n* YBN Luigi\n* YBN DVD\n* YBN r0yal\n* YBN Declan\n* YBN Swarn\n* YBN Mirr\n* YBN Naim\n* YBN Antsu\n* YBN Future Savage\n* YBN WOODRYC\n* YBN 5cxxt\n* YBN Ray\n{{Div col end}}\nDeceased members:\n* YBN Valley\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Mixtapes ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+ List of mixtapes, with selected chart positions and details\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:19em;\" | Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\" | Peak chart po